<topic id="configure-transformation-dialog">
  <title>Configure Transformation Scenario(s) Dialog Box</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Transformation Scenarios<indexterm>Configure Transformation Scenario dialog
            box</indexterm></indexterm>
        <indexterm>Configure Transformation Scenario dialog box</indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p id="p_efm_cgk_54b">You can use the <uicontrol>Configure Transformation Scenarios(s)</uicontrol> dialog box for
        <xref href="edit-scenario-dialog.dita#edit-scenario-dialog">editing existing transformation
        scenarios</xref> or <xref
        href="defining-new-transformation-scenario.dita#defining-new-transformation-scenario"
        >creating new ones</xref>. </p>
    <p id="p_ffm_cgk_54b">To open this dialog box, use the <uicontrol><image href="../img/TransformConfig16.png"
          id="image_hcv_gwv_sr"/>Configure Transformation Scenario(s) (<shortcut
          conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/ctrl_shift_c_shortcut"
          product="author developer editor"/><shortcut
          conkeyref="reusable-oxygen-shortcuts-list/alt_shift_tc_shortcut"
          product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"/>)</uicontrol> action from the
      toolbar or the <menucascade product="author developer editor">
        <uicontrol>Document</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol>Transformation</uicontrol>
      </menucascade><uicontrol product="authorEclipse developerEclipse editorEclipse"
        >XML</uicontrol> menu.</p>
    <p id="p_gfm_cgk_54b">
      <fig id="figure-configure-transformation-scenario-oxygen">
        <title>Configure Transformation Scenario(s) Dialog Box</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_scenario_list_dialog.png"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p id="p_hfm_cgk_54b">The dialog box includes the following options and features:</p>
    <p id="p_ifm_cgk_54b">
      <dl id="dl_jfm_cgk_54b">
        <dlentry id="dlentry_kfm_cgk_54b">
          <dt>Search Filter Field</dt>
          <dd>You can begin typing text in the search field at the top of the dialog box to filter
            the scenarios shown in the table below this field.</dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry id="dlentry_lfm_cgk_54b">
          <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/Settings16.png" id="image_tjj_cxb_wmb"
              />Settings</uicontrol></dt>
          <dd>Use this drop-down to access the following options:<p id="p_mfm_cgk_54b">
              <dl id="dl_nfm_cgk_54b">
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/show-all-scenarios" id="dlentry_ofm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/scenarios-available-for-editor" id="dlentry_pfm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/show-associated-scenarios" id="dlentry_qfm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/import-scenarios-dlentry" id="dlentry_rfm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/export-selected-scenarios" id="dlentry_sfm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p></dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry id="dlentry_tfm_cgk_54b">
          <dt>Scenarios Table Section</dt>
          <dd>
            <p id="p_ufm_cgk_54b">The middle section of the dialog box is a table that displays the scenarios that you
              can apply to the current document.<ph product="author developer editor"> You can view
                both the scenarios associated with the current document type and the scenarios
                defined at <xref keyref="glossentry_project-options">project level</xref>.</ph> The
              table includes following sortable columns:<ul id="ul_i4h_kxb_wmb">
                <li id="li_vfm_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>Association</uicontrol> - The checkboxes in this column mark whether
                  or not a transformation scenario is associated with the current document.</li>
                <li id="li_wfm_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>Scenario</uicontrol> - This column presents the names of the
                  transformation scenarios.</li>
                <li id="li_xfm_cgk_54b"><uicontrol>Type</uicontrol> - If the <uicontrol>Show Type</uicontrol> contextual
                  menu option is selected, this column displays the type of the transformation
                  scenario. For further details about the types of transformation scenarios that are
                  available in <ph keyref="product"/>, see the <xref
                    href="edit-scenario-dialog.dita#edit-scenario-dialog/transformation_types"
                    >Transformation Types section</xref>.</li>
              </ul></p>
            <p id="p_yfm_cgk_54b">If you right-click in the header area, the following options are accessible:</p>
            <p id="p_zfm_cgk_54b">
              <dl id="dl_agm_cgk_54b">
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/show-type" id="dlentry_bgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/show-storage" id="dlentry_cgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/group-by-association"
                  product="author developer editor" id="dlentry_dgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/group-by-type" id="dlentry_egm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/group-by-storage" id="dlentry_fgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/ungroup-all" id="dlentry_ggm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/reset-layout" id="dlentry_hgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p>
            <p id="p_igm_cgk_54b">If you right-click any particular transformation scenario, the following actions are
              accessible:</p>
            <p id="p_jgm_cgk_54b">
              <dl id="dl_kgm_cgk_54b">
                <dlentry id="dlentry_lgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/Wrench16.png" id="image_q3v_wsc_wmb"
                      />Edit</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>This button opens the <xref
                      href="edit-scenario-dialog.dita#edit-scenario-dialog"><uicontrol>Edit
                        Scenario</uicontrol> configuration dialog box</xref> that allows you to
                    configure the options of the transformations scenario.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_mgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/Copy16.png" id="image_r3v_wsc_wmb"
                      />Duplicate</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Use this button to create a <xref
                      href="duplicating-transformations.dita#duplicating-transformations">duplicate
                      transformation scenario</xref>.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_ngm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol><image href="../img/Remove16.png" id="image_s3v_wsc_wmb"
                      />Remove</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Use this button to remove custom transformation scenarios.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry product="author developer editor" id="dlentry_ogm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Change storage</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Allows you to change the storage location of a transformation scenario to
                      <xref keyref="glossentry_project-options"><uicontrol>Project
                        Options</uicontrol></xref> or <xref keyref="glossentry_global-options"
                        ><uicontrol>Global Options</uicontrol></xref>. You are also able to keep the
                    original storage location and make a copy of the selected scenario in the new
                    storage location.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/import-scenarios-dlentry" id="dlentry_pgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry conkeyref="reusables-transforming-documents/export-selected-scenarios" id="dlentry_qgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt/>
                  <dd/>
                </dlentry>
              </dl>
            </p>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
        <dlentry id="dlentry_rgm_cgk_54b">
          <dt>Bottom Section</dt>
          <dd>
            <p id="p_sgm_cgk_54b">The bottom section of the dialog box contains the following actions and options:<dl id="dl_tgm_cgk_54b">
                <dlentry id="dlentry_ugm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>New</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>This button allows you to <xref
                      href="defining-new-transformation-scenario.dita#defining-new-transformation-scenario"
                      >create a new transformation scenario</xref>.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_vgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>This button opens the <uicontrol>Edit Scenario</uicontrol> dialog box that
                    allows you to configure the options of the transformations scenario. For
                    information about all the specific options in the various tabs, see the <xref
                      href="edit-scenario-dialog.dita#edit-scenario-dialog/transformation_types"
                      >Transformation Types section</xref>.<note id="note_wgm_cgk_54b">If you try to edit a transformation
                      scenario associated with a defined document type, <ph keyref="product"/>
                      displays a warning message to inform you that this is not possible and gives
                      you the option to create a <xref
                        href="duplicating-transformations.dita#duplicating-transformations"
                        >duplicate transformation scenario</xref> to edit instead. </note></dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_xgm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Duplicate</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Use this button to create a <xref
                      href="duplicating-transformations.dita#duplicating-transformations">duplicate
                      transformation scenario</xref>.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_ygm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Remove</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Use this button to remove transformation scenarios.<note id="note_zgm_cgk_54b">Removing scenarios
                      associated with a defined document type is not allowed.</note></dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_ahm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Association follows selection</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Select this checkbox to automatically associate selected transformation
                    scenarios with the current document. This option can also be used for multiple
                      selections.<note id="note_bhm_cgk_54b">When this option is selected, the
                        <uicontrol>Association</uicontrol> column is hidden.</note></dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_chm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Run in parallel (DITA-OT or Ant scenarios)</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>This option is available if you select multiple DITA-OT or Ant type scenarios.
                    Selecting this option results in the transformations being done in parallel,
                    instead of sequentially. It should help to reduce the amount of time it takes
                    for the publishing to finish when transforming large projects.<note
                      type="attention" id="note_dhm_cgk_54b">If multiple selected DITA-OT scenarios have the same output
                      or temporary files folder, this option is not available since the process
                      would need to read and write content to the same folder in this
                    case.</note></dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_ehm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Associated scenarios</uicontrol> section </dt>
                  <dd>Displays the scenarios that are associated with the current document.
                    Selecting a checkbox in the <uicontrol>Association</uicontrol> column in the
                    list of scenarios will add that scenario to this section. To remove a scenario
                    from being associated with the current document, simply click the remove icon
                        (<uicontrol><image href="../img/Remove16.png" id="image_bj5_btc_wmb"
                      /></uicontrol>) to the right of the scenario name.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_fhm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Save and close</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Saves the current configuration and closes the dialog box.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_ghm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Apply associated</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Use this button to apply the associated scenarios and run the transformation
                    on the current document.</dd>
                </dlentry>
                <dlentry id="dlentry_hhm_cgk_54b">
                  <dt><uicontrol>Cancel</uicontrol></dt>
                  <dd>Cancels any changes made in the dialog box and reverts to the previously saved
                    association.</dd>
                </dlentry>
              </dl></p>
          </dd>
        </dlentry>
      </dl>
    </p>
    <note type="tip" id="note_ihm_cgk_54b">Your selections in the <uicontrol>Configure Transformation
        Scenarios(s)</uicontrol> dialog box are persistent so the configured associations for the
      current document will be remembered after the dialog box is closed.</note>
  </body>
